title: Compiler runs out of stack

labels.name: A-runtime
labels.description: Area: std's runtime and "pre-main" init for handling backtraces, unwinds, stack overflows

labels.name: I-crash
labels.description: Issue: The compiler crashes (SIGSEGV, SIGABRT, etc). Use I-ICE instead when the compiler panics.

body:
tar.gz version of 0.3.1

Trying to compile the following program fails:

``` rust
class trie_node {
    let mut content: ~[str];
    let mut children: ~[trie_node];

    new () {
        self.content = ~[];
        self.children = ~[];
    }
}

fn print_str_vector(vector: ~[str]) {
    for vector.each() |string| {
        io::println(string);
    }
}

fn main() {
    let node: trie_node = trie_node();
    let v = ~["123", "abc"];
    node.content = ~["123", "abc"];
    print_str_vector(v);
    print_str_vector(node.content);

}
```
